---
import Layout from '../../layouts/Layout.astro';
import PageHero from '../../components/PageHero.astro';
import ImageText from '../../components/ImageText.astro';
import BookingCTA from '../../components/BookingCTA.astro';
---
<Layout
	title="Children & Young People"
	description="Specialist physio for children and young people — Vojta therapy, developmental movement support and teenage sports injury management."
>
	<PageHero
		title="Children & Young People"
		breadcrumb="Children & Young People"
	/>

	<ImageText
		image="/who-we-help/kids-playing-football.jpg"
		imageAlt="Group of children running and playing football outdoors"
	>
		<p>Children and young people have unique developmental needs that require specialist care. At Balance, we work with children from infancy through adolescence, addressing developmental movement disorders, neurological conditions and the sports injuries that come with an active childhood and teenage years.</p>
	</ImageText>

	<ImageText
		reverse
		altBg
		image="/who-we-help/toddler-smiling.jpg"
		imageAlt="Smiling toddler playing in a playground"
	>
		<p>Vojta therapy is at the heart of our work with infants and younger children. This specialist neurophysiological approach is used in the treatment of cerebral palsy, developmental delay, plagiocephaly and scoliosis. Early intervention is critical. The younger a child begins therapy, the greater the nervous system's capacity to develop healthy movement patterns. We work closely with families, teaching parents techniques to continue therapy at home between sessions for consistent, sustainable progress.</p>
	</ImageText>

	<ImageText
		image="/who-we-help/young-women-stretching.jpg"
		imageAlt="Young women stretching together outdoors before training"
	>
		<p>For teenagers, academy members and sports scholars, sports injuries require careful management that accounts for how the developing body differs from an adult's. Growth plate issues, overuse injuries and the effects of early sports specialisation v the ranges of maturation are areas our physiotherapists and podiatrists handle with real expertise.</p>
	</ImageText>

	<ImageText
		reverse
		altBg
		image="/who-we-help/girl-kicking-football.jpg"
		imageAlt="Young girl concentrating as she kicks a football"
	>
		<p>At Balance, treating a child means working with the whole family. We communicate clearly, involve parents and carers fully throughout, and create an environment where children feel safe, supported and motivated to engage with their rehabilitation.</p>
	</ImageText>

	<BookingCTA />
</Layout>
